SECTION 5 — RULES
════════════════════════════════════════════════════

1. background: transparent on :host — global particle 
   canvas must show through. Do NOT add any solid 
   background color to this component.

2. NO phase filtering, NO tabs that hide systems.
   ALL phases visible simultaneously as columns.
   This is a MAP not a filter UI.

3. Single accent color: #00C896 everywhere.
   No purple, green, orange, red, grey per phase.
   Color parity with landing page is mandatory.

4. grid-template-columns: repeat(6, 1fr) on desktop —
   all 6 phases side by side. Do NOT reduce to fewer
   columns unless viewport is below 1024px.

5. sys-card animation uses CSS @keyframes card-enter
   with animation-delay set inline via [style].
   Do NOT use *ngIf toggling or JS setTimeout for
   the entrance animation — CSS handles it entirely.

6. Back button uses router.navigate(['/']) — NOT
   location.back() or history.back(). Those break
   if the user arrived directly at /ecosystem via URL.

7. phase-header has position: sticky, top: 0 — 
   phase labels stay visible as user scrolls down
   through long system lists (especially Recruit 
   which has 14 systems).

8. workday-badge hidden on mobile (display:none at 
   640px) to keep the banner clean on small screens.

9. topbar-spacer has the same implicit width as 
   .back-btn — this is what keeps .eco-title-block 
   visually centered. Do NOT remove it or the title 
   will drift left on desktop.

10. Add CommonModule and RouterModule to the component's
    module imports if *ngFor or routerLink cause errors.
11. Use better icons from any website if possible otherwise use whats stated

